  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-13667">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13667 mb-requirement-id-13668">
        (a) Describe how a properly working plumbing system protects your
        family's health and safety. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/MVGgjYigmDE?si=nwaqXmHn2CuYYAnK"
          target="_blank"
          >How Plumbing Transformed Public Health (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13667 mb-requirement-id-13669">
        (b) List five important local health regulations related to plumbing and
        tell how they protect health and safety.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13667 mb-requirement-id-13670">
        (c) Describe the safety precautions you must take when making home
        plumbing repairs. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/gyWrbmQp5a0?si=mSS8s25KUFkV39Z5"
          target="_blank"
          >Plumbing Safety Tips (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-13671">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      Do the following: <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/8jxRn-T_LCs?si=pwjNJvf0MCXM5gdY" target="_blank"
        >How Your Home Plumbing Works (From Start to Finish) (video)</a
      >
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13671 mb-requirement-id-13672">
        (a) Make a drawing and explain how a home hot- and cold-water supply
        system works. Tell how you would make it safe from freezing.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13671 mb-requirement-id-13673">
        (b) Make a drawing and explain the drainage system of the plumbing in a
        house. Show and explain the use of drains and vents.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-13677">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      Show how to use five important plumber's tools. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/uppuvS8BShU?si=a2SBD-wzgASkoSy2" target="_blank"
        >6 Essential Plumbing Hand Tools...and Others to Keep Around! (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-13678">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      Identify and explain the following terms: washer, retaining nut, plunger
      (rubber force cup), solder, flux, elbow, tee, nipple, coupling, plug,
      union, trap, drainpipe, and water meter.
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-13679">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 5. </span>
      Name the kinds of pipe that are used most often in a plumbing system.
      Explain why these pipes are used. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/OJkj4T9_X9I?si=b2eBR2WGlANFrxyF" target="_blank"
        >Four Types of Pipes Explained! (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-13680">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 6. </span>
      Do FOUR of the following, each under the supervision of a knowledgeable
      adult:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13680 mb-requirement-id-13682">
        (a) Visit the plumbing section of a hardware store or home center and
        identify:
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13682 mb-requirement-id-13683">
        1. PVC pipe and fittings
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13682 mb-requirement-id-13684">
        2. CPVC pipe and fittings
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13682 mb-requirement-id-13685">
        3. PEX pipe and fittings
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13682 mb-requirement-id-13686">
        4. Copper pipe and fittings
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13682 mb-requirement-id-13687">
        5. Steel pipe and fittings
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13682 mb-requirement-id-13688">
        6. Specialty plumbing tools.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13680 mb-requirement-id-13689">
        (b) Cut, clean (debur), PVC or CPVC pipe; solvent weld at least three
        connections to include a coupling, tee, and elbow. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/gSNlq7QK8lc?si=DhCkTPDDKnnF_d0R"
          target="_blank"
          >How To Cut, Prime &amp; Cement PVC Pipe &amp; Fittings Like A PRO
          (How To Bond PVC) Solvent Weld PVC (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13680 mb-requirement-id-13690">
        (c) Cut PEX pipe; make at least one connection using either a
        quick-connect fitting or a crimp fitting (using specialized tools).
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/vpnp3RayEPI?si=iieOezZIhF4ePAB-"
          target="_blank"
          >How To Cut And Crimp Pex - From A Professional (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13680 mb-requirement-id-13691">
        (d) Solder a copper connection using a gas torch. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/TOtOpixWTXE?si=Jl_jeHOlvComjB_k"
          target="_blank"
          >Copper Pipe Soldering-How to Solder for Beginners Video (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13680 mb-requirement-id-13692">
        (e) Replace a kitchen or lavatory faucet. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/hyTeVMYgRM0?si=Vjs95F0m6dK-Ae11"
          target="_blank"
          >Women's DIY Bathroom Remodel (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13680 mb-requirement-id-13693">
        (f) Remove, clean or replace, and reinstall a sink or lavatory drain
        trap. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/OFui97xhln0?si=0j-wNeNigMTLVJHt"
          target="_blank"
          >How To Install P-Trap And Bathroom Sink Drain Piping | Easy
          Installation For Beginners! (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13680 mb-requirement-id-13694">
        (g) Properly apply pipe thread tape to a pipe or a plumbing connector.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/KJoO87dW30U?si=zlN2wJ1V8ciBaLEt"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Apply Teflon Tape Like a Plumbing Pro (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
